S.B. 445
SENATE BILL NO. 445–COMMITTEE ON EDUCATION
MARCH 24, 2025
____________
Referred to Committee on Education
SUMMARY—Revises provisions relating to the privacy of data
concerning pupils. (BDR 34-854)
FISCAL NOTE: Effect on Local Government: May have Fiscal Impact.
Effect on the State: Yes.
~
EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to education; requiring the Department of
Education to transfer certain data concerning pupils to the
Division of State Library, Archives and Public Records of
the Department of Administration; requiring the Division
to destroy such data after a certain period of time; and
providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires the Department of Education to establish an automated
2 system of accountability information that records and tracks certain data relating to
3 the education system, including, without limitation, a system of unique
4 identification for each pupil and the results of the achievement of pupils. (NRS
5 385A.800) Existing law requires the board of trustees of each school district to
6 collect and provide certain data concerning pupils, as prescribed by the
7 Superintendent of Public Instruction, to the Department of Education. (NRS
8 385A.810, 385A.820)
9 Existing law establishes: (1) the Division of State Library, Archives and Public
10 Records of the Department of Administration; (2) the position of State Library,
11 Archives and Public Records Administrator; and (3) the duties of the
12 Administrator. (NRS 232.213, 378.010-378.130) This bill requires the Department
13 of Education to: (1) not later than 1 year after a pupil graduates from a high school
14 or otherwise ceases enrollment in a public school in this State, transfer any data
15 concerning the pupil to the Division; and (2) redact any personally identifiable
16 information from the data before making such a transfer.
17 Existing law: (1) creates the Committee to Approve Schedules for the Retention
18 and Disposition of Official State Records; (2) requires the Committee to review and
19 approve or disapprove the schedules for the retention and disposition of the official
20 state records of each agency, board and commission that is required to create such
21 schedules; and (3) prohibits an official state record from being disposed of in a
22 manner other than the schedule approved by the Committee. (NRS 239.073,
23 239.077, 239.080, 378.320) This bill requires: (1) that any data concerning pupils
